270
00:18:49,799 --> 00:18:52,949
I can't even get a minute's break.

271
00:18:52,949 --> 00:18:54,719
I'm coming!

272
00:18:54,719 --> 00:18:58,049
Sorry to keep you when you're busy. Bye for now.

273
00:19:16,559 --> 00:19:20,429
I could hear her voice even from the car.

274
00:19:20,429 --> 00:19:21,979
Let's eat there one day.

275
00:19:21,979 --> 00:19:24,749
- She seems nice.
- Sounds good.

276
00:19:46,559 --> 00:19:50,069
Gil Nakwon, what do you think? Isn't it nice?

277
00:19:50,069 --> 00:19:53,559
Do you regret saying you didn't want to move here?

278
00:19:53,559 --> 00:19:55,739
I left all my friends back in Seoul.

279
00:19:55,739 --> 00:19:57,179
It would be strange not to regret it.

280
00:19:57,179 --> 00:19:59,299
You can make new friends here.

281
00:19:59,299 --> 00:20:02,639
Meet your Seoul friends when you visit the city.

282
00:20:02,639 --> 00:20:05,289
You're not 10 or 12 years old anymore.

283
00:20:05,289 --> 00:20:09,209
You shouldn't be upset about this. You're all grown up.

284
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:11,259
Sometimes, you say I'm grown up.

285
00:20:11,259 --> 00:20:13,589
Sometimes, you say I'm young and clueless.

286
00:20:13,589 --> 00:20:16,549
She always changes her mind, right, Lucky?

287
00:20:27,869 --> 00:20:30,569
Namu, today at school,

288
00:20:30,569 --> 00:20:34,939
my teacher told me that I drew very well.

289
00:20:35,009 --> 00:20:36,689
Aren't you proud of me?

290
00:20:36,749 --> 00:20:39,389
I am. What did you draw?

291
00:20:39,389 --> 00:20:42,659
I drew Mom, you, and me.

292
00:20:42,659 --> 00:20:44,289
Our family.

293
00:20:44,289 --> 00:20:47,589
What about Dad and Hyeonmu?

294
00:20:47,659 --> 00:20:49,919
I didn't draw them yet.

295
00:20:49,919 --> 00:20:53,959
I can't remember what Dad looks like.

296
00:20:53,959 --> 00:20:55,669
You see him every day.

297
00:20:55,669 --> 00:20:59,039
Still, I can't remember well.

298
00:20:59,039 --> 00:21:04,469
Does he look happy, or does he look angry?

299
00:21:04,469 --> 00:21:05,779
What about Hyeonmu?

300
00:21:05,779 --> 00:21:09,249
I didn't draw him because I didn't want to.

301
00:21:09,249 --> 00:21:12,079
He always curses at you and hits you.

302
00:21:12,079 --> 00:21:16,409
If he hits you again and keeps doing that to you,

303
00:21:16,409 --> 00:21:19,959
then I'll run up to him

304
00:21:19,959 --> 00:21:23,389
and bite his hand.

305
00:21:23,389 --> 00:21:26,919
You should have included them. They're family.

306
00:21:26,919 --> 00:21:30,659
I only need you and Mom.

307
00:21:30,659 --> 00:21:33,739
If I'm with you and Mom,

308
00:21:33,739 --> 00:21:37,179
I'll be happy every day.

309
00:21:46,719 --> 00:21:51,159
Hey. I told you not to bark at people!

310
00:21:51,159 --> 00:21:54,199
Namu, what's that?

311
00:21:54,199 --> 00:21:55,959
It's okay. It's a dog.

312
00:21:55,959 --> 00:21:58,559
Dad, Lucky.

313
00:22:06,469 --> 00:22:10,869
Sorry, kid. Did you get scared? Sorry.

314
00:22:47,219 --> 00:22:50,579
Sorry, kid. I'll punish him when we get home.

315
00:22:50,579 --> 00:22:54,979
Sorry. Hey, you come here. Hey. Hey, hey!

316
00:23:04,699 --> 00:23:08,559
Wow, that dog is huge and pretty.

317
00:23:08,559 --> 00:23:10,969
Namu, the girl next to the dog...

318
00:23:10,969 --> 00:23:13,559
was really pretty too, right?

319
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:16,109
Yes, she was.

320
00:23:16,109 --> 00:23:20,109
What kind of a dog gets so big?

321
00:23:20,109 --> 00:23:23,839
It looks like a Golden Retriever. They're smart and gentle.

322
00:23:23,839 --> 00:23:26,989
If they're trained well, they're good guard dogs.

323
00:23:26,989 --> 00:23:29,889
If I meet that dog when I'm in danger,

324
00:23:29,889 --> 00:23:33,919
will it protect me, too?

325
00:23:33,919 --> 00:23:36,859
Sohjin, I'll protect you.

326
00:23:36,859 --> 00:23:39,269
Wherever you are and from anyone.

327
00:23:39,269 --> 00:23:43,759
Then in return, I will protect you, too.

328
00:23:43,759 --> 00:23:46,699
Wherever you are and from anyone.

329
00:23:46,699 --> 00:23:50,749
That's why you have to stay with me at all times.

330
00:23:50,749 --> 00:23:54,849
Forever and ever, okay?

331
00:23:54,849 --> 00:23:58,589
Okay. I will for sure do that.

332
00:24:17,759 --> 00:24:19,459
What's the matter?

333
00:24:31,449 --> 00:24:34,959
- What are you staring at?
- What?

334
00:24:34,959 --> 00:24:37,729
Our luggage.

335
00:24:37,729 --> 00:24:40,649
There's a lot of luggage.

336
00:24:40,649 --> 00:24:41,989
What did you say?

337
00:24:41,989 --> 00:24:45,299
What? I meant...

338
00:24:46,519 --> 00:24:48,699
Never mind.

339
00:24:50,859 --> 00:24:52,839
The cherry blossom petals.

340
00:24:52,839 --> 00:24:57,929
They look like snowflakes.

341
00:24:57,929 --> 00:25:01,039
I never thought our daughter would say something so poetic.

342
00:25:01,039 --> 00:25:04,249
I raised her for 16 years, and it's my first time hearing it.

343
00:25:04,249 --> 00:25:06,789
Geez, not a big deal.

344
00:25:06,789 --> 00:25:09,119
Yes, you are.

345
00:25:21,499 --> 00:25:23,129
Hey guys.

346
00:25:23,129 --> 00:25:25,009
That's our house.

347
00:25:50,089 --> 00:25:53,739
Do you mean that white, isolated house on the hill?

348
00:25:53,739 --> 00:25:55,989
Yes, that two-story house.

349
00:25:55,989 --> 00:25:59,059
It was Ji Hyewon who renovated that house.

350
00:25:59,059 --> 00:26:02,029
Why would a celebrity move to a countryside like this?

351
00:26:02,029 --> 00:26:03,169
Maybe she has no money.

352
00:26:03,169 --> 00:26:06,009
No, she has a house in Seoul.

353
00:26:06,009 --> 00:26:07,569
This would be a summer house.

354
00:26:07,569 --> 00:26:10,609
She came here to take a break for few years.

355
00:26:10,609 --> 00:26:11,919
You know what?

356
00:26:11,919 --> 00:26:15,089
This area is known for clean air and water.

357
00:26:15,089 --> 00:26:18,879
She must have so much money that she needs to spend it.

358
00:26:18,879 --> 00:26:20,589
A summer house?

359
00:26:20,589 --> 00:26:23,499
Listen! When I saw her earlier,

360
00:26:23,499 --> 00:26:26,289
she looked like an angel. So incredibly beautiful!

361
00:26:26,289 --> 00:26:27,999
She had plastic surgery.

362
00:26:27,999 --> 00:26:30,739
All celebrities get several surgeries nowadays.

363
00:26:30,739 --> 00:26:32,829
They get nose jobs and make their eyes bigger.

364
00:26:32,829 --> 00:26:35,969
Even I could become an actress.

365
00:26:36,839 --> 00:26:39,509
Really? You should give it a try.

366
00:26:39,599 --> 00:26:44,009
Ji Hyewon is known for her natural beauty.

367
00:26:44,009 --> 00:26:48,419
I don't have enough money for food. I can't even get eyebrow tattoos.

368
00:26:48,419 --> 00:26:52,649
- Auntie!
- Yes, I'm coming.

369
00:26:52,649 --> 00:26:56,969
To be honest, I'm quite pretty.

370
00:26:56,969 --> 00:27:00,659
My husband says that he fell in love with me at first sight.

371
00:27:00,669 --> 00:27:03,099
He's a riot.

372
00:27:04,559 --> 00:27:08,169
You're the one who's a riot.

373
00:27:10,679 --> 00:27:12,679
Enjoy your food.

374
00:27:12,679 --> 00:27:16,909
Gosh, I really like how friendly you are.

375
00:27:18,449 --> 00:27:22,219
- Here you go.
- You don't need to tip me.

376
00:27:22,219 --> 00:27:24,619
88 Lights, please.

377
00:27:24,619 --> 00:27:26,959
- Pardon?
- 2 packs.

378
00:27:26,959 --> 00:27:30,059
Right. Menthol, please.

379
00:27:31,929 --> 00:27:35,989
Unni, I'm going to the market to buy cigarettes for a customer.

380
00:27:35,989 --> 00:27:40,559
2 packs of 88 Lights in menthol.

381
00:27:40,559 --> 00:27:44,679
[Soondae, suyuk]

382
00:27:47,679 --> 00:27:50,679
Why're you back? I told you not to come here.

383
00:27:50,679 --> 00:27:54,019
Sohjin keeps looking for you.

384
00:27:56,259 --> 00:27:58,289
I put her to sleep over there.

385
00:28:04,589 --> 00:28:06,999
Give it to me. I'll go and buy them.

386
00:28:06,999 --> 00:28:08,489
Do you even know what to buy?

387
00:28:08,489 --> 00:28:12,009
2 packs of 88 Lights in menthol.

388
00:28:12,029 --> 00:28:15,209
No, they won't sell to kids.

389
00:28:17,749 --> 00:28:22,649
You look terrible. The collar looks so filthy.

390
00:28:24,989 --> 00:28:28,059
A big group is coming tonight, so you can't eat nor study here.

391
00:28:28,059 --> 00:28:29,619
Just go on home already.

392
00:28:29,619 --> 00:28:31,859
Don't forget to prepare dinner for your father.

393
00:28:31,859 --> 00:28:33,689
Okay.

394
00:28:34,659 --> 00:28:36,049
[Busan Lady's Pork Soup]

395
00:28:36,049 --> 00:28:38,359
Eat the fritters in the fridge.

396
00:28:38,359 --> 00:28:40,199
Make fried eggs for yourselves.

397
00:28:40,199 --> 00:28:44,059
Even though I'm not home, eat well. Okay?

398
00:28:44,059 --> 00:28:47,969
Okay. Remember to eat your dinner, too.

399
00:28:49,620 --> 00:28:53,440
[Busan Lady's Pork Soup]

400
00:28:53,449 --> 00:28:55,809
Why's that boy so thin?

401
00:28:55,809 --> 00:28:58,849
He should be eating anything at his age.

402
00:29:02,079 --> 00:29:03,389
That girl...

403
00:29:03,429 --> 00:29:07,759
Why does she act like a baby when she's nine years old?

404
00:29:07,759 --> 00:29:11,269
That's why her brother's so weak.

405
00:29:11,319 --> 00:29:13,329
He's too thin.

406
00:29:14,239 --> 00:29:15,459
My goodness.

407
00:29:15,469 --> 00:29:19,239
The problem with one son is that he's got a temper.

408
00:29:19,239 --> 00:29:21,779
The other one is too naive.

409
00:29:21,779 --> 00:29:23,369
- How could Changmin...
- Seriously.

410
00:29:23,369 --> 00:29:26,649
- Hello, girls.
- Hello.

411
00:29:26,649 --> 00:29:29,639
- They're pretty.
- My legs hurt.

412
00:29:29,639 --> 00:29:31,539
- Hey, girls.
- What is he doing?

413
00:29:31,539 --> 00:29:33,309
- What?
- You're pretty.

414
00:29:33,309 --> 00:29:35,459
- Hello.
- Hi.

415
00:29:35,459 --> 00:29:36,989
- What is it?
- What's that?

416
00:29:36,989 --> 00:29:39,649
Does it talk about how to make a girlfriend?

417
00:29:42,289 --> 00:29:45,089
- Where are you going?
- Where are you off to?

418
00:29:45,089 --> 00:29:48,359
- Hey, hey.
- Where are you going?

419
00:29:56,649 --> 00:29:57,839
Let's go to an internet cafe.

420
00:29:57,839 --> 00:30:00,939
- Let's go.
- Come on.

421
00:30:00,939 --> 00:30:02,879
What's going on?

422
00:30:04,009 --> 00:30:05,209
Wait a sec.

423
00:30:05,279 --> 00:30:07,079
- Where are you going?
- Where are you going?

424
00:30:07,079 --> 00:30:09,589
- Let's go.
- Where are you going?

425
00:30:09,589 --> 00:30:11,679
Where's he going?

426
00:30:11,679 --> 00:30:14,589
Geez.

427
00:30:16,429 --> 00:30:19,169
You punk, it's dangerous. What if you get hurt?

428
00:30:19,169 --> 00:30:22,869
Where are you going? Did you go around in the morning?

429
00:30:22,869 --> 00:30:26,159
I'm going to this one place in Seoul. Why?

430
00:30:30,069 --> 00:30:33,409
We're going to an internet cafe. Can I get some money?

431
00:30:35,679 --> 00:30:39,109
Punk, you always ask.

432
00:30:39,109 --> 00:30:42,249
- Come home for dinner.
- Okay.

433
00:30:46,699 --> 00:30:48,559
Listen.

434
00:30:48,559 --> 00:30:52,999
Make some pleasant looking friends. All of them look bad.

435
00:30:54,239 --> 00:30:55,399
- See you.
- All right.

436
00:30:55,399 --> 00:30:58,729
- I'll be home early.
- Okay.

437
00:31:00,639 --> 00:31:03,639
I told you to be careful!

438
00:31:25,589 --> 00:31:28,629
Sir, have some of this.

439
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:33,929
I only need a glass of water.

440
00:31:33,929 --> 00:31:35,869
You went to the supermarket?

441
00:31:35,869 --> 00:31:37,549
It's close by.

442
00:31:37,549 --> 00:31:41,069
- You're my customer.
- Thank you.

443
00:31:42,009 --> 00:31:44,839
Does the water go down well now?

444
00:31:44,839 --> 00:31:46,309
Turn it on.

445
00:31:46,309 --> 00:31:49,609
